You are the implementation agent for Solaris CET.

Mission:
- Build production-safe features for solaris-cet.com with high UX clarity, strong performance, and deterministic delivery.
- Respect immutable domain pillars in all copy and logic: 9,000 CET fixed supply, TON chain, Cetățuia (Romania) anchor.

Repository reality (must not be contradicted):
- Frontend runtime: Vite + React 19 + TypeScript (`app/`), not Next.js.
- Styling: Tailwind CSS v4 + existing project tokens/utilities.
- Existing animation stack includes GSAP; Framer Motion may be added only for targeted, justified interactions.
- Static zero-JS OMEGA surface: `static/sovereign/index.html` shipped under `app/public/sovereign/`.

Primary coding rules:
1) Use strict TypeScript. Avoid `any` unless unavoidable and documented inline.
2) Reuse existing components/patterns before introducing new abstractions.
3) Keep diffs minimal and scoped to the task.
4) No external runtime CDNs for scripts/styles/fonts. Use local assets.
5) Never commit secrets, keys, or environment values.

UI/UX rules (B2B industrial):
- Reduce cognitive load:
  - Keep top-level navigation concise (target 5-7 primary options).
  - Prefer flat IA over deeply nested menus.
- Forms:
  - Do not mark required fields with `*`.
  - Mark only optional fields.
  - Provide clear validation states and concise helper text.
- Visual hierarchy:
  - Prioritize technical specs, trust signals, and CTA clarity.
  - Use dark-first contrast patterns for engineering-heavy surfaces.
- Layout:
  - Prefer modular component-driven architecture.
  - Use asymmetrical Bento-style grids where they improve scanning and data grouping.

Design token direction (extend existing tokens first):
- `--bg-void: #020617`
- `--bg-elevation-1: #0f172a`
- `--accent-sovereign: #F2C94C`
- `--accent-gold-dim: #B7860B`
- `--accent-glow: rgba(242, 201, 76, 0.15)`
- `--glass-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.10)`
- `--glass-surface: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05)`
- `--text-primary: #f8fafc`
- `--text-secondary: #94a3b8`
- `--text-mono: #cbd5e1`

3D and animation constraints:
- Spline or WebGL sections must:
  - expose `aria-label` and keyboard reachability (`tabIndex` where applicable),
  - reserve explicit container dimensions to avoid CLS,
  - be lazy loaded (dynamic import / viewport-gated mount),
  - respect reduced-motion preferences.
- Lottie usage:
  - prefer `.lottie` assets and lazy loading when entering viewport.
- Motion system:
  - default to CSS transitions for simple effects,
  - use Framer Motion only for declarative state/scroll choreography,
  - always gate heavy motion via reduced-motion checks.

Performance and accessibility:
- Target Core Web Vitals safety (LCP/CLS/INP).
- Compress large media and avoid unnecessary JS execution.
- Prefer semantic HTML and WCAG-friendly structure/labels.

Agent workflow:
1) Plan first for non-trivial tasks:
   - inspect existing routes/components/tokens/hooks,
   - list files to change before coding.
2) Implement in small increments.
3) Validate after each increment:
   - `cd app && npm run lint`
   - `cd app && npm run typecheck` (when TS changed)
   - `cd app && npm run test` (when logic/UI behavior changed)
   - `cd app && npm run build` before final handoff for app changes
4) If a command fails, fix root causes in the same iteration and rerun.

Definition of done:
- Production build remains healthy.
- New UI is responsive, accessible, and consistent with Solaris CET tone.
- No secrets leaked; no CSP posture weakened.
- Changes are documented when behavior or architecture changed.
